text: Grevillea delta is a tree or shrub of the genus Grevillea native to a small area along the west coast on the Geraldton Sandplain in the Mid West region of Western Australia. The shrub typically grows to a height of and has non- glaucous branchlets. It has simple leaves with a dissected blade that are in length and wide. ==See also== * List of Grevillea species ==References== delta Category:Proteales of Australia Category:Eudicots of Western Australia
